  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat the oven to 180°C. Drop the whole potatoes into a large pot of salted water – they should be just covered with water. Bring to the boil, then reduce to a simmer and cook for 10 - 15 mins until parboiled, a knife should slide through but don’t take them too far or they’ll turn to mush when you crush them. Drain and leave in the colander for 2 mins."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Tip the potatoes onto a large baking tray lined with baking parchment. Press the potatoes flat using the bottom of a glass. Drizzle with olive oil, salt and pepper. Roast in the oven for 40-50 mins until really crispy on the edges."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Meanwhile, slice the cucumber lengthwise and scoop out and discard the middle – this is to prevent the sauce from getting watery. Finely chop the dill and chives."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Transfer the chopped herbs and cucumber to a bowl along with the remaining ingredients and a pinch of salt and pepper. Mix well and set aside."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Once the potatoes are really crispy, remove from the oven and stir them through the sauce. Garnish with sliced spring onions and crispy onions – enjoy!"
    }
  ],
